CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 12, 1941, pg. 8, reads: "The Willard Jeffersons - Miss Helen L. Brown and Willard M. Jefferson were married June 28th by the Rev. T. J. King. A pretty reception was held at the Northside Elks' Hall.  The couple left for an Eastern honeymoon.  The bride is the daughter of the Arthur Browns; the groom, the son of the Clarence Jeffersons. - (Harris photo).
TitMainTitle: Bride Helen L. Brown Jefferson wearing gown with sheer feather pattern and long train, and groom Willard M. Jefferson, posed in interior with venetian blind and floral curtains
